WEBVTT

00:01.131 --> 00:03.133
Woman: So far, what we know

00:03.177 --> 00:04.743
is that the fire stated
somewhere...[ Dog barking in distance ]

00:04.787 --> 00:06.484
...in the Santa Clarita hills
late last night

00:06.528 --> 00:09.139
and quickly spread
throughout the area.

00:09.183 --> 00:11.446
Local fire crews worked
throughout the night...[ Footsteps approach quickly ]

00:11.489 --> 00:13.143
...establishing
a containment zone

00:13.187 --> 00:15.493
in hopes of protecting
several neighborhoods

00:15.537 --> 00:19.410
including one in Sylmar, where
residents were placed under...

00:19.454 --> 00:23.023
-Hello.
-What are you doing here?

00:23.066 --> 00:24.415
My house.

00:24.459 --> 00:26.678
Funny. Last time I checked,
I live here.

00:26.722 --> 00:28.202
According to
the Probate Division

00:28.245 --> 00:29.899
of the Los Angeles
Superior Court --

00:29.942 --> 00:31.814
Dad, we went
over and over this.

00:31.857 --> 00:33.424
Robert wanted to fix
this place up.

00:33.468 --> 00:35.209
That's what I'm gonna do.That's what you said
two years ago

00:35.252 --> 00:37.472
when you made them
transfer you here.

00:37.515 --> 00:38.734
I didn't make them
transfer me.

00:38.777 --> 00:41.215
You know what?
Let's start over.

00:41.258 --> 00:43.956
Looks like you haven't
gotten very far.Hey, Dad. It's been a while.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.610
How is the short game?[ Knock on door ]

00:45.654 --> 00:48.874
Just a minute.It's gonna be hot as ass
out there today, so --

00:48.918 --> 00:50.702
-Oh.
-Rox.

00:50.746 --> 00:54.141
-Meet my dad.
-Colonel Martin Willis.

00:54.184 --> 00:55.620
-[ Clears throat ]
-And you are...

00:55.664 --> 00:57.709
Roxanne Valenzuela.
Nice to meet you.Girlfriend?

00:57.753 --> 01:01.104
She's pretty.Partner
and an excellent paramedic.

01:01.148 --> 01:03.237
I'm, uh, standing right here,
guys.

01:03.280 --> 01:05.195
Partners? Four years
of medical school,

01:05.239 --> 01:08.285
3 years residency,
and 20 years in the military,

01:08.329 --> 01:09.939
and now you're a medic?

01:09.982 --> 01:12.898
Having a doctor on site
dramatically increases
survival rates.

01:12.942 --> 01:15.162
And that's why you're
doing this?Why else would I do it?

01:15.205 --> 01:17.512
There's a 4,000-acre blaze
in Santa Clarita.[ Helicopter whirring ]

01:17.555 --> 01:18.904
The governor issued
a state of emergency.

01:18.948 --> 01:20.906
We're being deployed
to the fire line.

01:20.950 --> 01:23.431
-What the hell's that?
-That's our ride.

01:23.474 --> 01:27.696
[ Whirring continues ]

01:27.739 --> 01:29.698
Your patient came in
with head trauma,

01:29.741 --> 01:33.441
but you didn't order a CT scan
until hours later. Why?

01:33.484 --> 01:34.877
Detective Gomez
refused treatment.

01:34.920 --> 01:37.880
At that point, did you
assess his capacity

01:37.923 --> 01:39.534
for making decisions?

01:39.577 --> 01:41.231
Uh...what do you mean?

01:41.275 --> 01:43.364
Never answer a question
with a question.

01:43.407 --> 01:45.453
The officer took a bullet
to the head, Dr. Dixon.

01:45.496 --> 01:47.324
Did it occur to you that
he might have suffered

01:47.368 --> 01:50.458
traumatic brain injury,
keeping him from understanding

01:50.501 --> 01:52.460
the severity
of his situation?

01:52.503 --> 01:53.939
I'm pretty sure
he understood, but --You're pretty sure?

01:53.983 --> 01:56.203
-I don't hear any certainty.
-Enough.

01:56.246 --> 01:58.248
Keep your responses
short and declarative.

01:58.292 --> 02:00.816
He's not ready.That's why we practice
with him.

02:00.859 --> 02:02.905
Look, I am grateful
for your help,

02:02.948 --> 02:04.646
but I've been thinking
about this lawsuit,

02:04.689 --> 02:07.736
and if I'm really responsible
for the death of my patient,

02:07.779 --> 02:10.260
then I want to accept
the consequences.

02:12.262 --> 02:14.395
You have a responsibility
to this hospital.

02:14.438 --> 02:17.615
Now your crisis of conscience
could cost this institution

02:17.659 --> 02:19.400
millions of dollars
it doesn't have.

02:19.443 --> 02:20.966
Do you understand?

02:21.010 --> 02:24.231
Yeah.

02:24.274 --> 02:28.496
[ Whirring ]

02:28.539 --> 02:30.498
Did we figure out
what sparked this thing?

02:30.541 --> 02:32.587
Hippies smoking weed
near the campgrounds.

02:32.630 --> 02:34.371
Legal in 30 states.

02:34.415 --> 02:36.417
When we get down there,
leave the firefighting to us.

02:36.460 --> 02:37.766
Someone gets hurt,
you treat them.

02:37.809 --> 02:39.289
Otherwise, for the next
24 hours,

02:39.333 --> 02:42.553
you stay close,
remember your escape routes.

02:42.597 --> 02:45.513
-Keep one foot in the black.
-You've done this before.

02:45.556 --> 02:47.776
I was a line medic
for the Agoura Hotshots.

02:47.819 --> 02:49.517
Then you've seen these.

02:49.560 --> 02:51.301
Fire shelter.

02:51.345 --> 02:52.781
In case we get caught
in a burnover.

02:52.824 --> 02:56.524
-Those things actually work?
-Sometimes.

02:56.567 --> 02:58.265
♪♪

02:58.308 --> 03:00.267
[ Exhales deeply ]

03:00.310 --> 03:02.443
[ Whirring ]

03:02.486 --> 03:05.533
-Well, pupils look normal.
-[ Groans ]

03:05.576 --> 03:06.969
How long has this
been going on?

03:07.012 --> 03:08.797
Uh, I've had stomach cramps
for three days,

03:08.840 --> 03:12.409
plus nausea, blood in my poop,
and fever of 104.

03:12.453 --> 03:16.979
-I would say ischemic colitis.
-[ Imitates buzzer ] Wrong.

03:17.022 --> 03:19.634
What? Let me see that?

03:19.677 --> 03:22.419
-Okay, fine. You're right again.
-Ha ha!

03:22.463 --> 03:23.812
Why are you so worried
about this test?

03:23.855 --> 03:25.683
You can pass it
in your sleep.

03:25.727 --> 03:28.817
Because I want to stay
board-certified
for the next 10 years,

03:28.860 --> 03:31.602
and because there's always
a question that you never
see coming.

03:31.646 --> 03:33.300
-Challenge accepted.
-Bring it on.

03:33.343 --> 03:35.867
-We got incoming, Daddy.
-Thanks, babe.

03:35.911 --> 03:37.652
[ Elevator bell dings ]

03:37.695 --> 03:38.914
Is that another one
from the wildfire?

03:38.957 --> 03:40.698
Dr. Rorish,
meet Bridget Kozelek,

03:40.742 --> 03:43.745
28 years old, chainsaw injury
to the upper shoulder.

03:43.788 --> 03:47.314
Hotshot with the Forest Service.How are you feeling, Bridget?

03:47.357 --> 03:49.751
I feel like I almost cut
my arm off with a chainsaw.

03:49.794 --> 03:52.319
Axillary artery laceration,
but she just started
having trouble breathing.

03:52.362 --> 03:54.582
All right, let's get her
center stage.

03:54.625 --> 03:55.931
-Coming through, people.
-Heads up. Watch your backs.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.325
Okay. Rail down.[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:58.368 --> 04:00.588
Okay, Bridget, your throat
is swelling.

04:00.631 --> 04:02.851
It's a delayed reaction
from the burns.

04:02.894 --> 04:05.027
We need to get ahead of it
and put a breathing tube
down your throat, okay?

04:05.070 --> 04:08.378
Wait. You need to call my dad --
Hank Kozelek.

04:08.422 --> 04:10.380
-He's a captain, LAFD.
-Okay.

04:10.424 --> 04:11.947
-Got it.
-I'm on it.

04:11.990 --> 04:14.036
-Pushing RSI meds now.
-Dr. Dixon, that is too slow.

04:14.079 --> 04:16.734
She needed that five seconds
ago. Let's go, let's go! Okay?

04:16.778 --> 04:18.040
This fireman's
peak pressures are too high.

04:18.083 --> 04:19.607
See this thick burn
on his chest wall?

04:19.650 --> 04:21.826
It's constricting his lungs.
What's your next move?

04:21.870 --> 04:23.872
Cut under the muscle to release
the tension so he can breathe?

04:23.915 --> 04:26.483
You've got 30 seconds, tops.
Let's go.

04:26.527 --> 04:28.572
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:28.616 --> 04:29.747
♪♪

04:29.791 --> 04:30.922
Come on.

04:30.966 --> 04:32.533
♪♪

04:32.576 --> 04:34.665
Okay. Take a breath...
and then take control.

04:34.709 --> 04:38.060
Realize what you're doing wrong
and adjust.

04:38.103 --> 04:40.018
Keep going.

04:40.062 --> 04:41.368
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

04:41.411 --> 04:43.892
Sats are 60% and dropping.

04:43.935 --> 04:46.764
I-I just can't get it. It keeps
hitting the top of --

04:46.808 --> 04:49.376
Dr. Avila, one shot. Let's go.

04:49.419 --> 04:50.551
[ Rapid beeping continues ]

04:50.594 --> 04:51.856
I see cords.

04:51.900 --> 04:53.771
Look here?

04:53.815 --> 04:55.686
[ Rapid beeping continues ]

04:55.730 --> 04:57.384
-I'm in.
-There you go.

04:57.427 --> 04:58.733
[ Rapid beeping continues ]

04:58.776 --> 05:00.778
[ Beeping stops ]

05:00.822 --> 05:03.128
Cuts are...complete.

05:03.172 --> 05:04.956
Still no signs
of chest rise.

05:05.000 --> 05:06.697
Okay, pop him off the vent.
Let's give him
some manual breaths.

05:06.741 --> 05:08.786
Faster, faster,
faster, faster.

05:08.830 --> 05:10.875
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

05:10.919 --> 05:13.530
-There it is.
-Good chest rise. It's working.

05:13.574 --> 05:14.923
He's breathing.All right, prep him
for the O.R.

05:14.966 --> 05:16.881
It's Vista Verde School,
urgent about your daughter.

05:16.925 --> 05:18.448
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:18.492 --> 05:19.667
Go ahead. Hello?

05:19.710 --> 05:23.148
Okay. Is...Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

05:23.192 --> 05:25.760
♪♪

05:25.803 --> 05:29.154
Get him up to the OR.
I'll be there in a few.

05:29.198 --> 05:32.114
[ Indistinct conversations,
monitors beeping ]

05:32.157 --> 05:37.554
[ Sirens wailing,
helicopter whirring ]

05:37.598 --> 05:39.426
Bravo crew's suppressing
a spot fire

05:39.469 --> 05:41.123
1/2 mile east of here.
Guys, let's pick up the pace.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.994
♪♪

05:43.038 --> 05:45.127
Hold up.

05:45.170 --> 05:46.868
[ Helicopter whirring ]

05:46.911 --> 05:48.913
What is it?

05:48.957 --> 05:50.132
[ Man yelling faintly ]Guys, hear that?

05:50.175 --> 05:51.960
Do you hear that?

05:52.003 --> 05:54.571
Man: Caleb!

05:54.615 --> 05:56.704
-Caleb!
-Hey!

05:56.747 --> 05:58.140
Caleb!

05:58.183 --> 05:59.924
Hey!

05:59.968 --> 06:01.491
What are you doing here?
This area's supposed
to be evacuated.

06:01.535 --> 06:02.884
I need help. I need help.

06:02.927 --> 06:05.060
-Let me look at this arm.
-No, I need to find him.

06:05.103 --> 06:07.149
Find who?

06:07.192 --> 06:09.891
My boy. Please.
He's still out there.

06:09.934 --> 06:11.719
We have to find him.

06:11.762 --> 06:14.504
[ Coughing ] Caleb!

06:14.548 --> 06:15.549
♪♪

06:23.861 --> 06:26.168
Left arm has bruising
and swelling,

06:26.211 --> 06:28.997
possible fracture. Distally
and neurovascularly intact.

06:29.040 --> 06:30.520
I have to find Caleb.

06:30.564 --> 06:32.043
I know you're upset,
but right now I need you
to calm down.

06:32.087 --> 06:34.698
-He's 6 years old.
-See the guy over there?

06:34.742 --> 06:36.047
He's on the phone
with Search and Rescue.

06:36.091 --> 06:37.658
We're doing everything
we can do.

06:37.701 --> 06:39.529
How'd you guys get separated,
anyway?

06:39.573 --> 06:42.837
-We were camping off-trail.
-Off-trail? With a 6-year-old?

06:42.880 --> 06:45.883
The second we saw smoke,
we headed downhill.

06:45.927 --> 06:49.713
The decline was steep.
I fell. I hit my head.

06:49.757 --> 06:52.586
When I woke up,
Caleb was gone.

06:52.629 --> 06:53.935
This was supposed to be
my chance to make up

06:53.978 --> 06:55.719
for missing his birthday again.

06:55.763 --> 06:56.981
It's my dumb luck
this fire broke out

06:57.025 --> 06:58.548
the weekend I brought
Caleb here.

06:58.592 --> 07:00.550
Probably didn't help it was
the peak of fire season.

07:00.594 --> 07:02.247
I'm not exactly Mr. Outdoors,
all right?

07:02.291 --> 07:04.119
Okay, he probably went for help.

07:04.162 --> 07:06.556
All right, so Cal Fire
is dispatching a chopper
to comb the area.

07:06.600 --> 07:08.993
Wait, with this visibility?
All they'll see is smoke.

07:09.037 --> 07:12.257
She's right. That kid
won't survive unless
we put somebody on foot.

07:12.301 --> 07:14.085
Well, I can call in
a couple of my guys,

07:14.129 --> 07:16.261
break off a short squad.
-I'm coming with you. Aah!

07:16.305 --> 07:19.090
Whoa, whoa. Can you walk
on that leg?

07:19.134 --> 07:21.092
It's just a sprain.
You're gonna need me.

07:21.136 --> 07:25.270
I can show you where
we got separated. Caleb!

07:25.314 --> 07:27.925
[ Indistinct conversations ]Magazine?

07:27.969 --> 07:31.363
Hey, do you have anything
with actual words?

07:31.407 --> 07:34.323
These are just photos of
people famous for doing nothing.

07:34.366 --> 07:38.066
Oh, let me see what I can do.Yeah, years from now,
your generation will be known

07:38.109 --> 07:39.720
as the one
that killed journalism.

07:39.763 --> 07:42.331
Hey, man, I get it.
Magazines were different

07:42.374 --> 07:44.638
in your days before
the invention of the camera.[ Clears throat ]

07:44.681 --> 07:47.249
Oh, no, you again.Dr. Stoval,
nice to see you, too.

07:47.292 --> 07:50.513
We ran some tests.
Your hemoglobin count is low.

07:50.557 --> 07:52.602
I'm tired all the time,
bruise easily,

07:52.646 --> 07:56.084
and my bone marrow isn't making
healthy blood cells anymore.

07:56.127 --> 07:59.087
-An intern could make the call.
-It's Myelodysplasia.

07:59.130 --> 08:03.091
-It's a type of blood cancer.
-See what I mean?

08:03.134 --> 08:05.746
I'm helping Leanne study
for her recertification.

08:05.789 --> 08:08.096
So I'm just gonna go
stand over there.

08:08.139 --> 08:09.271
That's a good idea.

08:09.314 --> 08:11.360
Spare me the HemOnc lecture,
kid.

08:11.403 --> 08:13.101
I've forgotten more about
medicine than you'll ever know.

08:13.144 --> 08:15.495
Wouldn't be doing my job if I
didn't mention your options.

08:15.538 --> 08:17.279
Keep your
bone marrow transplant.

08:17.322 --> 08:18.672
We both know I'm end stage.

08:18.715 --> 08:22.414
I'm just living out my last days
with dignity.

08:22.458 --> 08:24.155
Well, that's your decision
to make.

08:24.199 --> 08:26.157
You're damn right it is,
so cut to the part

08:26.201 --> 08:29.770
where you hand me a clipboard
and I sign the DNR

08:29.813 --> 08:31.815
and whatever else you got.
Soon as the drip is done,

08:31.859 --> 08:34.122
I'm going home.

08:34.165 --> 08:36.254
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

08:36.298 --> 08:37.604
Wait. Hey, Savetti, wait up.

08:37.647 --> 08:39.475
Pretty sure there's a "Doctor"
in front of that.

08:39.519 --> 08:41.608
So what's a "DNR"?

08:41.651 --> 08:44.524
It's, uh...nothing you need
to worry about.

08:44.567 --> 08:49.790
♪♪

08:49.833 --> 08:52.532
[ Helicopter whirring ]

08:52.575 --> 08:54.185
Any of this look familiar?

08:54.229 --> 08:55.665
I remember that rock face.

08:55.709 --> 08:57.798
Maybe not.
It all looks the same.

08:57.841 --> 08:59.582
Are we even going
the right direction?

08:59.626 --> 09:02.324
-I...I think so.
-All right, we're a mile in.

09:02.367 --> 09:03.630
Let's just keep going.

09:03.673 --> 09:06.589
Caleb wanted to go
to a Dodgers game.

09:06.633 --> 09:09.549
I told him camping with his dad
is something he'd look back on.

09:09.592 --> 09:11.899
Figured he was just scared,
but you're supposed to

09:11.942 --> 09:15.163
throw 'em in the deep end.
That's what my dad did.

09:15.206 --> 09:18.470
-We're way past the deep end.
-Hey.

09:18.514 --> 09:21.343
Hey! Listen, we can't
be out here anymore.

09:21.386 --> 09:23.780
Wind's picking up.
Humidity's dropping.

09:23.824 --> 09:25.956
It's the witching hour.
Time of day when fire's
most unpredictable.

09:26.000 --> 09:29.264
We can't tell where
this thing's headed.I'm not leaving
without the kid.

09:29.307 --> 09:30.961
You go.
We'll keep looking.

09:31.005 --> 09:33.790
All right, you guys head back.
I'll stick around.

09:33.834 --> 09:35.487
You should go, too.
Get that leg looked at.

09:35.531 --> 09:38.403
No way.
Not without Caleb.

09:38.447 --> 09:41.058
[ Helicopter whirring ]

09:41.102 --> 09:43.800
Hey, man, we still cool?

09:43.844 --> 09:46.324
-Were we ever cool?
-This lawsuit's in your head.

09:46.368 --> 09:49.414
Easy for you to say.
I am the one being sued

09:49.458 --> 09:51.503
for us letting
an LAPD officer die.

09:51.547 --> 09:53.114
Yeah, no kidding it's in
my head. And you know what?

09:53.157 --> 09:55.943
I don't need you one-upping me
in front of Rorish.

09:55.986 --> 09:57.945
♪♪

09:57.988 --> 09:59.424
We had to intubate
your daughter,

09:59.468 --> 10:02.210
but she's had other injuries.
-Part of the job.

10:02.253 --> 10:03.994
Let me see my girl.

10:04.038 --> 10:06.301
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over PA ]

10:06.344 --> 10:07.868
[ Sighs ]

10:07.911 --> 10:12.960
She also has a large tear
in her axillary artery.

10:13.003 --> 10:15.832
They'll need to repair
in surgery.

10:15.876 --> 10:19.096
This wildfire is taxing
our resources,

10:19.140 --> 10:21.098
but I'll get her into an O.R.
as soon as possible.

10:21.142 --> 10:24.493
Can I get you a chair?
Mr. Kozelak?

10:25.363 --> 10:27.844
Can I get you a chair?

10:27.888 --> 10:30.586
No, I'll stand.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.589
Look at her.
Still beautiful.

10:33.633 --> 10:37.027
Doesn't matter
what you throw at her.

10:37.071 --> 10:40.901
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:40.944 --> 10:43.251
[ Footsteps depart ]

10:43.294 --> 10:46.863
[ Exhales deeply ] Well, at
least I'm getting my steps in.

10:46.907 --> 10:49.561
The rare upside
to a forest fire.

10:49.605 --> 10:52.303
So what's up with you
and your dad?

10:52.347 --> 10:54.131
-What do you mean?
-I don't know.

10:54.175 --> 10:56.568
You just seem a little on edge
today, that's all.

10:56.612 --> 10:58.353
Just focused.

10:58.396 --> 11:01.312
Somehow I never imagined
you having a father.

11:01.356 --> 11:03.575
You think I hatched?

11:03.619 --> 11:04.881
[ Chuckles ] Yes.

11:04.925 --> 11:07.057
Hold on! [ Coughs ]

11:07.101 --> 11:09.277
Hey, you gotta stop
walking on that leg.

11:09.320 --> 11:13.063
Yeah, I know. Just hold on.
I think this place --

11:13.107 --> 11:15.196
-it looks...
-You and Caleb were here?

11:15.239 --> 11:19.896
-Yes, I think we were here.
-Hey, got a body over here.

11:19.940 --> 11:21.245
-Oh, God. I can't look.
-All right. Stay there.

11:21.289 --> 11:26.598
I can't...
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:26.642 --> 11:30.167
♪♪

11:30.211 --> 11:32.909
[ Whispers ] Oh, my God.
Oh, God.

11:32.953 --> 11:34.041
[ Breathing heavily ]

11:34.084 --> 11:38.088
♪♪

11:38.132 --> 11:40.482
-It's not Caleb.
-[ Gasps ]

11:40.525 --> 11:42.440
♪♪

11:42.484 --> 11:44.442
Probably got caught out here
while hunting.

11:44.486 --> 11:47.924
Tried to outrun
a burnover.

11:47.968 --> 11:50.405
[ Gasping ]

11:50.448 --> 11:51.449
♪♪

11:57.412 --> 11:58.630
I'm not getting on
that helicopter!

11:58.674 --> 12:02.112
I can't leave Caleb! Not again!

12:02.156 --> 12:03.940
He must be so scared!

12:03.984 --> 12:05.768
You got an injured arm,
banged-up leg.

12:05.812 --> 12:08.466
You inhaled a lot of smoke.
You're just slowing us down.

12:08.510 --> 12:10.947
I'm not getting
on that helicopter.Yes, you are.

12:10.991 --> 12:12.775
Forced evacuation's
in effect.

12:12.819 --> 12:14.908
We're all getting outta here.[ Helicopter whirring ]

12:14.951 --> 12:17.432
Can I talk to you for a second?

12:17.475 --> 12:19.782
What if it was your son?

12:19.826 --> 12:21.479
And you knew he was still
out here?

12:21.523 --> 12:23.786
Kid's been missing for five
hours in an active wildfire.

12:23.830 --> 12:25.092
I gotta play the odds here.
That's the job.

12:25.135 --> 12:28.443
Okay, I don't work for you.
I'm staying.

12:28.486 --> 12:30.619
There's a 6-year-old boy
out there.

12:30.662 --> 12:32.142
I'm staying, too.

12:32.186 --> 12:35.493
If you get into trouble, I don't
know if I can get you out.

12:35.537 --> 12:38.714
I accept the risk.

12:38.758 --> 12:41.021
Good luck.

12:41.064 --> 12:42.805
You're gonna need it.[ Pats arm ]

12:42.849 --> 12:46.548
[ Helicopter whirring ]

12:53.685 --> 12:55.122
I know you're heading
out of town,

12:55.165 --> 12:57.472
but this is my daughter
we talked about.

12:57.515 --> 13:00.605
Can you cover --
Just tonight.

13:00.649 --> 13:03.043
Fine. [ Under breath ]
Damn it.

13:03.086 --> 13:05.393
Everything okay?
On a personal level?

13:05.436 --> 13:07.177
Asking as a friend.

13:07.221 --> 13:09.397
Dr. Leighton, what gave
the impression we were friends?

13:09.440 --> 13:12.182
Hello?
Yeah, Dr. Campbell here.

13:12.226 --> 13:15.795
Woman: Okay, we got burn victims
coming in.28-year-old male, third degree
burns all over his body.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.361
-Barely a pulse.
-All right, well, let's get him

13:17.405 --> 13:18.406
to center stage. He's not gonna
have one much longer.

13:18.449 --> 13:19.929
Dr. Rorish?

13:19.973 --> 13:23.846
[ Sighs ] Her case worker.
I forgot. Um...

13:23.890 --> 13:26.327
Grab Dr. Guthrie.
I'll be there in a minute.

13:26.370 --> 13:28.764
The home visit. I'm sorry.
Things got a little crazy here.

13:28.808 --> 13:32.072
Doctor, the foster-to-adopt
process is complicated enough --

13:32.115 --> 13:34.422
I promise you, nothing is more
important to me than Ariel.

13:34.465 --> 13:37.120
But I have a critical patient --I have a few calls I can make,
but this interview

13:37.164 --> 13:39.775
needs to happen today.
-All right! Got it! Today.

13:39.819 --> 13:42.125
Male, unknown age,
with full-thickness burns,

13:42.169 --> 13:45.259
TBSA approaching 100%.
They lost the pulse in the air.

13:45.302 --> 13:46.869
-Okay, Dr. Avila, we need --
-Terrence White, 34.

13:46.913 --> 13:49.176
Labored breathing
from the fire exposure

13:49.219 --> 13:52.788
plus leg and arm injuries.Hyperbaric chamber is
on standby if he makes it.

13:52.832 --> 13:54.921
Yeah, we need oxygen, fluids!
CO levels.

13:54.964 --> 13:57.053
I'm gonna need you
to take deep breaths
and stay calm, all right?

13:57.097 --> 13:58.838
Now I understand you were
camping with your son?

13:58.881 --> 14:00.796
That's right. Your people
are still out there.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.450
They're still looking for him.

14:02.493 --> 14:04.844
Doctor, doctor? A second.

14:04.887 --> 14:06.019
[ Monitor beeping ]

14:06.062 --> 14:07.847
-Rox and Willis, right?
-Yeah.

14:07.890 --> 14:09.849
We offered them a ride out,
but they're hard-heads.

14:09.892 --> 14:11.328
You have no idea.

14:11.372 --> 14:12.852
I do, actually. I get why
they're risking their lives.

14:12.895 --> 14:14.201
We all want to see
that kid alive,

14:14.244 --> 14:16.072
but I've been down this road
before. He's dead.

14:16.116 --> 14:17.857
What did he say?!Okay, you have to stand back,
please.

14:17.900 --> 14:19.249
You don't know that!

14:19.293 --> 14:21.382
-He doesn't know that!
-All right, lie back.

14:21.425 --> 14:24.037
If Dr. Willis thinks
that your son is alive,

14:24.080 --> 14:26.213
then so do I,
and so should you.

14:26.256 --> 14:29.129
But right now, I just need you
to breathe.

14:29.172 --> 14:30.391
Okay, just let this
help you breathe.

14:30.434 --> 14:33.133
[ Breathing heavily ]

14:33.176 --> 14:36.179
Come on. [ Panting ][ Monitor beeping erratically ]

14:36.223 --> 14:38.051
No pulse.
How long's he been down for?

14:38.094 --> 14:40.140
25 minutes.

14:40.183 --> 14:41.489
[ Palm pumping ]

14:41.532 --> 14:44.100
Okay. We're going to have
to call it.

14:44.144 --> 14:47.364
Time of death --
10:47 A.M.

14:47.408 --> 14:49.323
All right. Let's go.

14:49.366 --> 14:51.542
His sat isn't rising.
We need to intubate
before his airway closes.

14:51.586 --> 14:53.414
No, he just needs oxygen.

14:53.457 --> 14:55.851
I evaluated his airway
on the way down.

14:55.895 --> 14:56.939
Get him breathing treatments
and steroids.

14:56.983 --> 14:58.071
Hold it.

14:58.114 --> 15:00.029
BBG, please.

15:00.073 --> 15:01.204
[ Monitors beeping ]

15:01.248 --> 15:02.858
Dr. Avila is right.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.816
125 milligrams solumedrol
and continuous nebs.

15:04.860 --> 15:06.557
Then we're gonna see
what's going on with his leg.

15:06.601 --> 15:09.212
Dr. Dixon...

15:09.256 --> 15:13.216
Try not to insert things
into your patient unnecessarily.

15:13.260 --> 15:16.741
Got it? Med school 101.

15:16.785 --> 15:18.743
[ Curtain rings swoosh ]Okay, time for your walk.

15:18.787 --> 15:20.745
[ Scoffs ] I'm a patient,
not a puppy.

15:20.789 --> 15:22.704
You don't need to walk me.

15:22.747 --> 15:24.924
Ooh. Sick burn.

15:24.967 --> 15:27.056
How old are you?

15:27.100 --> 15:28.579
I'm 14.

15:28.623 --> 15:31.060
I have a granddaughter
just your age.

15:31.104 --> 15:33.149
She's equally vapid.

15:33.193 --> 15:35.064
Okay, here's this.

15:35.108 --> 15:37.980
Come for a walk,
and I'll get off your lawn.

15:38.024 --> 15:40.069
[ Indistinct conversations ][ Chuckles ]

15:40.113 --> 15:43.638
Mild wheezing bilaterally.
Let's get some albuterol

15:43.681 --> 15:45.770
and atrovent in, Risa.
-This one --

15:45.814 --> 15:47.163
always the first boot
through the door.

15:47.207 --> 15:49.252
She's strong, no doubt,
but her fight isn't over.

15:49.296 --> 15:51.776
I ran my home the same way
I ran my firehouse.

15:51.820 --> 15:54.170
I wasn't training heroes,
'cause you really can't.

15:54.214 --> 15:57.913
Can't have cowards, either,
not when you're running
into a fire.

15:57.957 --> 16:00.133
Who was gonna break and when?
Where was the limit?

16:00.176 --> 16:01.743
With Bridget, there was none.

16:01.786 --> 16:04.267
-No pulse in the distal arm.
-No pulse?

16:04.311 --> 16:08.315
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]She's bleeding. The compression
bandage isn't working.

16:08.358 --> 16:10.970
-Is she gonna lose her arm?
-We don't know that yet.

16:11.013 --> 16:13.885
She needs the O.R. I don't care
if they're ready for us,
but we're going up to surgery.

16:13.929 --> 16:16.149
Let's go!Jesse: Look out, people!
Coming through!

16:16.192 --> 16:19.152
I am back in negative-1.Can't talk right now.
I have 35 patients.

16:19.195 --> 16:20.762
You know how it is
with Campbell.

16:20.805 --> 16:22.024
You don't start at a zero.
You start in a hole,

16:22.068 --> 16:23.156
and the more you struggle
against that,

16:23.199 --> 16:25.114
the deeper you dig yourself.

16:25.158 --> 16:26.811
The problem is, you tried
to be his friend.

16:26.855 --> 16:28.639
-I overstepped?
-Who cares?

16:28.683 --> 16:31.120
Guarantee he's not
thinking about you...ever.

16:31.164 --> 16:34.689
-I should apologize.
-What? No. Manage up.

16:34.732 --> 16:36.169
He doesn't want your apology.
He wants your hard work.

16:36.212 --> 16:37.909
What, so I don't even
exist anymore?

16:37.953 --> 16:39.302
Seriously, Angus,
I can't deal right now.

16:39.346 --> 16:41.348
Oh, is that how it is?

16:41.391 --> 16:42.958
Yeah. You have your problems
upstairs.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.961
I have mine down here.
Excuse me.

16:46.005 --> 16:48.920
[ Indistinct conversations ]

16:48.964 --> 16:51.314
Look at them looking at me.

16:51.358 --> 16:53.316
I know that look.
I used to do that look.

16:53.360 --> 16:56.102
-What look?
-Dead man walking.

16:56.145 --> 16:58.930
Oh, I'm gonna walk
right outta here,

16:58.974 --> 17:02.717
because I certainly don't
wanna die in this...Hellhole?

17:02.760 --> 17:04.023
Vertical toilet.

17:04.066 --> 17:05.154
They can't keep me here,

17:05.198 --> 17:07.330
and they can't force
treatment on me.

17:07.374 --> 17:12.161
As soon as I got the stamina
to drive back to the Palisades,

17:12.205 --> 17:15.338
I'm outta here.
It's rush hour.

17:15.382 --> 17:17.732
I'm waiting out the traffic.

17:17.775 --> 17:19.690
You don't believe me.

17:19.734 --> 17:22.345
No, I don't believe
anyone's ever ready to die.

17:22.389 --> 17:23.955
You wouldn't understand,

17:23.999 --> 17:26.088
and you shouldn't argue
with your elders.

17:26.132 --> 17:29.048
My elders?
We're not pilgrims.

17:29.091 --> 17:31.137
And I never learned
manners anyway.

17:31.180 --> 17:33.095
Oh. I should speak
to your father.

17:33.139 --> 17:35.358
Sorry, he's dead.

17:35.402 --> 17:37.012
And mom, too.

17:37.056 --> 17:39.971
Oh, and my boyfriend Max --
he's got cancer.

17:40.015 --> 17:42.713
-I see.
-Oh, so you understand me,

17:42.757 --> 17:46.108
but you're this big mystery?
I don't think so, David.

17:46.152 --> 17:49.372
You're an odd one.

17:49.416 --> 17:51.722
♪♪

17:51.766 --> 17:53.376
[ Clatter ]David? Are you okay?

17:53.420 --> 17:55.422
Someone help!
He's having a heart attack!

17:55.465 --> 17:57.859
[ Grunting ]

17:57.902 --> 18:00.253
-Ariel! Get off him right now!
-No, get in here!

18:00.296 --> 18:02.429
He's DNR! Do Not Resuscitate!
Get off of him!

18:02.472 --> 18:05.388
No, get in here!
I've never done this before!

18:05.432 --> 18:09.218
Get off of him.No! Help him!
What's your problem?

18:09.262 --> 18:11.002
-Listen.
-[ Panting ]

18:11.046 --> 18:12.439
♪♪

18:12.482 --> 18:15.442
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-He's breathing, he's breathing.

18:15.485 --> 18:17.096
♪♪

18:17.139 --> 18:19.881
What did you do?

18:19.924 --> 18:22.927
-Caleb!
-Caleb!

18:22.971 --> 18:25.278
Never should have had
that kid out here.

18:25.321 --> 18:29.151
Oh, my job is 90% fixing people
after a bad decision.

18:29.195 --> 18:30.761
No sense judging.

18:30.805 --> 18:32.807
-His son's his responsibility.
-My experience --

18:32.850 --> 18:34.156
having a kid doesn't
make you an expert.

18:34.200 --> 18:36.593
-Just makes you a parent.
-Your experience?

18:36.637 --> 18:38.160
You got a kid that
you're hiding from me?

18:38.204 --> 18:40.989
[ Sighs ]
Professional experience.

18:41.032 --> 18:43.078
♪♪

18:43.122 --> 18:45.124
Something doesn't feel right.

18:45.167 --> 18:46.777
The wind just flipped.

18:46.821 --> 18:48.779
[ Leaves rustling,
wind blowing ]

18:48.823 --> 18:51.130
[ Explosion ]

18:51.173 --> 18:52.783
We gotta move!

18:52.827 --> 18:55.699
It's gonna be on us fast!

18:55.743 --> 18:59.007
[ Flames roar ]

18:59.050 --> 19:00.661
[ Flames crackling ]

19:00.704 --> 19:04.534
We can't outrun it!

19:04.578 --> 19:05.883
Willis, it's coming!

19:05.927 --> 19:10.845
[ Explosions, rumbling ]

19:10.888 --> 19:12.542
We're not gonna survive
a burnover!

19:12.586 --> 19:14.196
That's what this is for!
Come on! Get in!

19:14.240 --> 19:18.113
[ Flames crackling and roaring ]

19:21.247 --> 19:23.553
[ Gasping ]

19:23.597 --> 19:25.555
[ Grunting ]

19:25.599 --> 19:26.817
[ Crackling ]

19:26.861 --> 19:28.819
Okay, okay.

19:28.863 --> 19:30.952
It's getting hotter.
This thing might not save us.

19:30.995 --> 19:34.564
No matter what happens,
we stay in here.

19:34.608 --> 19:37.828
It'll work.
It has to work.

19:39.134 --> 19:40.701
Thank you. Okay.

19:40.744 --> 19:43.051
[ Breathing heavily ]

19:43.094 --> 19:45.140
Say...
[ Breathes heavily ]

19:45.184 --> 19:46.620
Say something hopeful.

19:46.663 --> 19:51.102
Anything. The poem
that your brother wrote.

19:51.146 --> 19:53.844
[ Breathing heavily ]
Tell me that.

19:53.888 --> 20:00.068
[ Breathing heavily ]

20:00.111 --> 20:02.853
Heart's petals wait
for morning hands,

20:02.897 --> 20:06.727
the smell of sunshine
at her doorstep.

20:06.770 --> 20:12.602
Tiny feet tickled
by Moroccan sands.

20:12.646 --> 20:15.257
She waltzes and tangos,

20:15.301 --> 20:18.129
and even a two-step.

20:18.173 --> 20:21.611
Pure as Tahitian blue,

20:21.655 --> 20:23.918
bright as Egyptian tan.

20:23.961 --> 20:28.270
Cured by a woman's hue,

20:28.314 --> 20:30.620
a sign
from the soul of man.

20:30.664 --> 20:33.623
♪♪

20:33.667 --> 20:39.150
Barefoot and young,
eyes tearing and wide.

20:39.194 --> 20:43.807
Words to be sung.

20:43.851 --> 20:46.332
Sky's clearing inside.

20:46.375 --> 20:48.986
[ Exhales deeply ]

20:49.030 --> 20:50.292
Because that is love.

20:50.336 --> 20:52.294
♪♪

20:52.338 --> 20:55.645
As you are love.

20:55.689 --> 20:57.125
As only love exists.

20:57.168 --> 20:58.909
[ Inhales and exhales deeply ]

20:58.953 --> 21:01.172
As hand in glove...

21:01.216 --> 21:04.175
As God above...

21:04.219 --> 21:06.090
As Heaven's song insists.

21:06.134 --> 21:09.050
♪♪

21:09.093 --> 21:13.184
-He was a romantic.
-He was.

21:13.228 --> 21:16.927
Who did he write that for?

21:16.971 --> 21:21.062
Whoever found it.
That's what he said.

21:21.105 --> 21:22.803
I like that.

21:22.846 --> 21:24.065
[ Flames rumbling ]Hang on.

21:24.108 --> 21:26.067
-[ Whimpers ] Ethan!
-Hang on!

21:26.110 --> 21:27.721
-Hang on!
-Oh!

21:33.117 --> 21:34.423
[ Wind blowing ]

21:34.467 --> 21:36.120
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

21:39.080 --> 21:40.864
Nothing over here!

21:40.908 --> 21:43.345
Keep looking!

21:43.389 --> 21:45.869
Right back to the line.

21:45.913 --> 21:49.090
♪♪

21:49.133 --> 21:51.353
I got two over here!

21:51.397 --> 21:53.964
-I got two over here!
-Where?!

21:54.008 --> 21:55.357
You okay?

21:55.401 --> 21:57.446
[ Men shouting indistinctly
in distance ]

21:57.490 --> 21:59.187
Man: Give him a hand!

22:02.321 --> 22:05.149
[ Coughs ]

22:05.193 --> 22:09.850
[ Both coughing ]

22:09.893 --> 22:12.983
What happened?The main fire
broke containment.

22:13.027 --> 22:14.855
We're scouring the area
for survivors.

22:14.898 --> 22:17.771
-[ Coughs ]
-You're lucky to be alive.

22:17.814 --> 22:19.163
♪♪

22:19.207 --> 22:21.165
You guys are the ones looking
for the missing kid.

22:21.209 --> 22:22.253
[ Coughing
and breathing heavily ]

22:22.297 --> 22:23.907
You find him?

22:23.951 --> 22:26.997
[ Panting ]

22:27.041 --> 22:29.130
[ Whispers ] No.

22:29.173 --> 22:30.914
Let's get you back
to the safe zone.

22:30.958 --> 22:32.873
♪♪

22:32.916 --> 22:34.788
Okay. Lead the way.

22:34.831 --> 22:38.748
♪♪

22:38.792 --> 22:41.882
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

22:41.925 --> 22:44.145
They're still working
on Bridget,

22:44.188 --> 22:47.409
but the damage to her artery
was worse than we thought.

22:47.453 --> 22:48.889
You said she was fine.

22:48.932 --> 22:51.413
-How bad is it?
-It's serious.

22:51.457 --> 22:54.242
Why didn't you do
something sooner?

22:54.285 --> 22:56.331
If I lose her,
that's on you.

22:56.375 --> 22:57.854
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

22:57.898 --> 23:00.509
[ Inhales deeply ]

23:00.553 --> 23:02.381
[ Elevator bell dings ]

23:02.424 --> 23:03.904
Hank, listen to me.

23:05.035 --> 23:06.559
This isn't your fault.

23:06.602 --> 23:09.866
I know that. You don't
have to tell me that.

23:09.910 --> 23:14.871
You didn't start
that fire.

23:14.915 --> 23:17.178
♪♪

23:17.221 --> 23:19.920
But I sparked
the one in her.

23:21.574 --> 23:24.881
She's...my little girl.

23:24.925 --> 23:27.057
I can't lose her.

23:27.101 --> 23:29.408
[ Sniffles ]

23:29.451 --> 23:32.889
She's not a little girl
anymore.

23:32.933 --> 23:35.239
She's in the best hands.
I'll keep you posted.

23:35.283 --> 23:38.939
Dr. Rorish? It's Ariel.

23:38.982 --> 23:40.244
How was I supposed to know
what a DNR is?

23:40.288 --> 23:41.550
I asked you,
and you didn't tell me.

23:41.594 --> 23:43.552
It's dumb anyway.
Who wants to die?

23:43.596 --> 23:45.119
It doesn't matter
what you think, Ariel.

23:45.162 --> 23:46.468
Of course it doesn't,
because then you would have

23:46.512 --> 23:49.079
to realize how crazy
you people sound, all of you.

23:49.123 --> 23:50.733
Ariel, no one is blaming you
for what happened.

23:50.777 --> 23:54.737
-You are not a doctor.
-Right. I'm just a kid.

23:54.781 --> 23:57.523
-Ariel...
-She's a candy striper, Leanne.

23:57.566 --> 23:58.828
She has no getting business
gettin anywhere close --

23:58.872 --> 24:01.048
You didn't explain it
to her?

24:01.091 --> 24:03.224
You are a third-year resident.
She's a volunteer.

24:03.267 --> 24:05.052
And you're her mother,
so why am I explaining

24:05.095 --> 24:06.880
end of life scenarios
to her?

24:06.923 --> 24:08.316
And why even teach her CPR
if you don't want her using it?

24:08.359 --> 24:09.578
-Angels isn't a daycare...
-Hey!

24:09.622 --> 24:11.319
And it's not my job
to raise your kid.

24:11.362 --> 24:13.147
-You better watch it!
-No, going forward,

24:13.190 --> 24:15.758
I need to know, am I speaking to
my boss or that girls' mother?

24:15.802 --> 24:20.197
You may leave my office.

24:20.241 --> 24:25.464
♪♪

24:25.507 --> 24:28.075
-Now is not a good time.
-You sure?

24:28.118 --> 24:30.686
Because I just heard a rumor
that a 14-year-old candy striper

24:30.730 --> 24:33.210
did CPR on a dying man.

24:33.254 --> 24:36.910
Ariel is an incredible
young woman.

24:36.953 --> 24:38.346
She has already faced
so much.

24:38.389 --> 24:40.914
She is equipped to handle
more than most.

24:40.957 --> 24:42.045
Still, is this the kind
of situation

24:42.089 --> 24:43.786
she should be facing?

24:43.830 --> 24:45.135
Are you saying she
shouldn't volunteer here?

24:45.179 --> 24:47.094
I'm questioning
the judgment of it.

24:47.137 --> 24:48.922
You mean, you're questioning
myjudgment.

24:48.965 --> 24:51.228
We both want what's best
for Ariel,

24:51.272 --> 24:52.360
but you should know that
I'm obligated

24:52.403 --> 24:54.667
to report this
to the court.

24:54.710 --> 25:00.673
♪♪

25:00.716 --> 25:04.285
[ Wind whistling ]

25:04.328 --> 25:07.114
I'll go with you when
you have to tell Terrence.

25:07.157 --> 25:08.811
You won't do it alone.

25:08.855 --> 25:12.728
[ Helicopter whirring ]

25:12.772 --> 25:14.948
My dad's here
to sell the house.

25:14.991 --> 25:17.037
It was Robert's.

25:17.080 --> 25:19.822
He's been struggling
with his death.

25:19.866 --> 25:21.084
He thinks getting rid
of the house

25:21.128 --> 25:23.130
will help him move on.

25:23.173 --> 25:24.435
What do youthink?

25:27.134 --> 25:29.005
Ranger Station.

25:29.049 --> 25:31.225
Would Terrence and Caleb

25:31.268 --> 25:34.054
pass the ranger station
on their hike up?

25:34.097 --> 25:37.405
Yeah, I think so.Where does a kid go when he's
lost at a supermarket?

25:37.448 --> 25:39.233
He looks for someone
who works there.

25:39.276 --> 25:41.148
I just wanna be able to say
that I did everything

25:41.191 --> 25:43.237
I can for that kid...

25:43.280 --> 25:45.718
and mean it.

25:45.761 --> 25:48.459
[ Helicopter roaring ]

25:48.503 --> 25:51.027
You guys go ahead. All right,
we'll meet you at base camp.

25:51.071 --> 25:53.073
All right, let's go.

25:53.116 --> 25:56.119
[ Monitor beeping steadily,
indistinct conversations ]

25:56.163 --> 25:58.426
You still don't feel that?

25:58.469 --> 26:01.472
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

26:01.516 --> 26:04.127
♪♪

26:04.171 --> 26:07.130
Dixon! Get over here.

26:07.174 --> 26:09.263
X-ray's showing
tibial plateau fracture.

26:09.306 --> 26:10.917
And now there's no
distal pulse.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.745
Compartment syndrome?
The swelling's cutting off

26:12.788 --> 26:14.224
circulation in his leg.
Page Campbell.

26:14.268 --> 26:17.140
-He's in surgery.
-It's a clinical diagnosis.

26:17.184 --> 26:18.925
-Do a fasciotomy.
-That's a surgical procedure.

26:18.968 --> 26:20.491
All right, We have time
for a consult.He could die.

26:20.535 --> 26:23.277
Just go. Save someone else.

26:23.320 --> 26:25.279
Sir, are you refusing
treatment?

26:25.322 --> 26:27.020
I don't deserve
to be alive.

26:27.063 --> 26:28.282
Okay, that's not
the same thing.

26:28.325 --> 26:30.110
-Hey, no, no, no, no.
-Sir.

26:30.153 --> 26:32.765
-No, no, no, no.
-[ Groaning ]

26:32.808 --> 26:35.506
[ Grunting ]Take it easy, all right?
Make the call!

26:35.550 --> 26:37.770
Dixon!

26:37.813 --> 26:40.773
Expose the proximal
and distal branches

26:40.816 --> 26:42.165
of the axillary artery.
-Dr. Campbell?

26:42.209 --> 26:44.037
It's Dr. Trenton
regarding your daughter.

26:44.080 --> 26:46.474
Come here, come here, come here.
Is she awake?

26:46.517 --> 26:49.825
Don't wake her. Just call me
every 20 minutes with an update.

26:49.869 --> 26:53.916
What? Why was she given access
to Emily's hospital room?

26:53.960 --> 26:55.309
No, that's not all right.

26:55.352 --> 26:58.312
You know what? I'll be there
soon as I can. God.

26:59.356 --> 27:01.402
How long is ischemic time?

27:01.445 --> 27:02.969
24 minutes.

27:03.012 --> 27:04.492
Hey, where is
the surgical attendant?

27:04.535 --> 27:06.233
-I can call her.
-Yes, try her again, please.

27:06.276 --> 27:08.496
I need the ETA.
More, Dr. Leighton.

27:08.539 --> 27:10.324
Excuse me, Dr. Campbell? I need
to run a patient by you.

27:10.367 --> 27:12.413
-Call a consult.
-No, it's time-sensitive.

27:12.456 --> 27:14.807
34-year-old male
with a tibial plateau fracture,

27:14.850 --> 27:17.113
no sensation in his foot,
no distal pulse.

27:17.157 --> 27:19.594
-Compartment syndrome.
-Okay, that's what I thought.

27:19.638 --> 27:21.204
Then why are you up here
and not down there
doing a fasciotomy?

27:21.248 --> 27:23.685
No, I-I just wanted
to make sure...Go!

27:23.729 --> 27:25.687
Yeah.

27:25.731 --> 27:27.820
♪♪

27:27.863 --> 27:30.953
Gonna go a little bit deeper.
Where were you?

27:30.997 --> 27:34.130
-I just went for a consult --
-Step back! Dr. Dixon.

27:34.174 --> 27:35.958
I mean it.

27:36.002 --> 27:39.745
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

27:39.788 --> 27:41.485
Let's go a little bit deeper
in there.

27:41.529 --> 27:43.836
Suction. You left him.

27:43.879 --> 27:46.708
You left your patient?
You knew what he needed.

27:46.752 --> 27:48.710
You knew it was urgent,

27:48.754 --> 27:51.495
and where did you go,
Dr. Dixon?

27:51.539 --> 27:53.672
-I just -- I wanted --
-This patient

27:53.715 --> 27:55.499
is no longer yours
to care for.

27:55.543 --> 27:57.066
Step away.

27:57.110 --> 28:00.983
[ Monitor beeping steadily,
suction whooshing ]

28:01.027 --> 28:02.855
-Got it?
-All right.

28:02.898 --> 28:05.205
[ Wind roaring ]

28:05.248 --> 28:07.163
Oh, no.

28:07.207 --> 28:08.643
Caleb!

28:08.687 --> 28:09.949
Look around the side.

28:09.992 --> 28:11.559
Caleb, are you in there?!

28:11.602 --> 28:13.996
♪♪

28:14.040 --> 28:16.869
-It's a kid's cap.
-He could be in there.

28:16.912 --> 28:18.871
[ Flames roaring ]

28:18.914 --> 28:21.830
[ Explosion, glass shatters ]

28:21.874 --> 28:23.571
♪♪

28:23.614 --> 28:25.007
Caleb!

28:25.051 --> 28:26.922
♪♪

28:26.966 --> 28:28.707
Caleb! [ Coughs ]

28:28.750 --> 28:30.012
[ Flames whoosh ]

28:30.056 --> 28:32.014
Willis!

28:32.058 --> 28:34.756
[ Flames roaring ]

28:34.800 --> 28:35.801
Willis!

28:35.844 --> 28:38.020
[ Coughing ] Caleb!

28:38.064 --> 28:41.197
Caleb: I'm here!

28:41.241 --> 28:42.721
[ Door bangs open ]

28:42.764 --> 28:45.201
Okay. Here. [ Coughing ]

28:45.245 --> 28:47.769
Here,
put this over your mouth!

28:47.813 --> 28:51.033
[ Coughing ]

28:51.077 --> 28:54.994
[ Flames roaring ]

28:55.037 --> 28:56.735
[ Coughs ]

28:56.778 --> 28:59.128
[ Glass shatters ]

28:59.172 --> 29:02.828
[ Flames roaring ]

29:03.872 --> 29:05.091
[ Coughing ]

29:05.134 --> 29:06.657
I'm coming.
I'm right behind you.

29:06.701 --> 29:08.790
[ Flames roaring ]

29:08.834 --> 29:10.052
[ Willis coughing ]

29:10.096 --> 29:12.576
Okay.

29:12.620 --> 29:15.666
Caleb! All right.

29:15.710 --> 29:17.581
Come on. Take a deep breath.
Come on, honey.

29:17.625 --> 29:18.757
Take a deep breath.

29:18.800 --> 29:20.062
There you go.

29:20.106 --> 29:22.064
[ Loud crash ]

29:22.108 --> 29:24.588
[ Flames crackling ]Willis?!

29:24.632 --> 29:26.634
[ Flames whoosh ]Willis!

29:32.161 --> 29:34.076
Willis!

29:34.120 --> 29:37.732
Okay. All right.
Be right back.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.255
Willis!

29:39.299 --> 29:40.953
[ Coughing ]

29:40.996 --> 29:45.131
Ethan! Ethan!

29:46.306 --> 29:48.047
♪♪

29:48.090 --> 29:49.744
[ Faintly ]
Stay with me. Stay with me.

29:49.788 --> 29:52.094
We're gonna get outta here,
okay?[ Coughing ]

29:52.138 --> 29:53.835
Come on. Get up with me.
Ready?

29:53.879 --> 29:56.272
One, two...
Here we go! Come on!

29:56.316 --> 29:57.926
Let's go!

29:57.970 --> 29:59.275
Come on! Come on!

29:59.319 --> 30:02.191
Let's get outta here!

30:02.235 --> 30:03.845
[ Door bangs ]

30:03.889 --> 30:08.197
[ Coughing ]

30:08.241 --> 30:14.203
[ Coughing continues ]

30:14.247 --> 30:20.601
♪♪

30:20.644 --> 30:22.864
Clamp it here.

30:22.908 --> 30:24.257
[ Door opens ]Hold still.

30:24.300 --> 30:26.650
Sorry. Clippers game.
110's a parking lot.

30:26.694 --> 30:28.391
Well, Lakers tickets on me,
then.

30:28.435 --> 30:29.871
We're just about done
with the primary repair

30:29.915 --> 30:31.742
of the axillary artery.

30:31.786 --> 30:35.137
Dr. Leighton's gonna fill you in
about the rest.

30:35.181 --> 30:38.314
He tell you what the family
emergency was about?

30:38.358 --> 30:42.144
We don't have that kind
of relationship.

30:42.188 --> 30:43.667
Can we check on a pulse,
please?

30:43.711 --> 30:47.149
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

30:47.193 --> 30:50.152
[ Steady pulsing ]

30:50.196 --> 30:51.762
That's it.

30:51.806 --> 30:54.548
-Bingo.
-Good work.

30:54.591 --> 30:56.767
Dr. Dixon.

30:56.811 --> 30:59.248
A word.

30:59.292 --> 31:01.163
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

31:01.207 --> 31:03.862
I can no longer
trust you with patients.

31:05.820 --> 31:08.867
Good, because I don't know
if I can trust me either.

31:08.910 --> 31:12.871
♪♪

31:12.914 --> 31:15.482
-He's a good doctor.
-He's a nice doctor.

31:15.525 --> 31:18.877
-I don't know if he's good.
-Yet.

31:18.920 --> 31:20.879
Which means we have
to give him a chance,

31:20.922 --> 31:22.489
not give up on him.

31:22.532 --> 31:25.884
I'll give him one week,

31:25.927 --> 31:27.886
and if it doesn't work,
he's out.

31:27.929 --> 31:33.456
♪♪

31:33.500 --> 31:37.373
I specifically told you not
to perform chest compressions.

31:37.417 --> 31:38.722
Dr. Stoval,
I'm very sorry,

31:38.766 --> 31:41.464
but there was a, um...
miscommunication.

31:41.508 --> 31:43.249
You violated my rights.

31:43.292 --> 31:45.381
Why?

31:45.425 --> 31:47.470
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

31:47.514 --> 31:49.472
Why do you wanna die?

31:49.516 --> 31:51.387
Ariel, I think you've done
enough for today.

31:51.431 --> 31:53.520
-Tell me.
-Come on.

31:53.563 --> 31:56.479
No, tell me. Tell me.

32:00.266 --> 32:02.616
It was you, wasn't it?

32:02.659 --> 32:08.709
♪♪

32:08.752 --> 32:16.586
♪♪

32:16.630 --> 32:18.719
40 years...

32:18.762 --> 32:20.808
I was the one they wanted
to see walking

32:20.851 --> 32:23.767
through
the operating room doors.

32:23.811 --> 32:27.423
They knew, and I was
in control no matter what.

32:27.467 --> 32:29.686
I was never scared.

32:29.730 --> 32:31.688
I never folded.

32:31.732 --> 32:34.735
And then one day I'm sitting
across from my best friend,

32:34.778 --> 32:38.652
and he tells me...

32:38.695 --> 32:40.697
I'm dying.

32:40.741 --> 32:43.657
It's over.

32:43.700 --> 32:53.667
♪♪

32:53.710 --> 32:57.279
I know everything that
this disease is doing to me

32:57.323 --> 32:59.325
down to the cell.

32:59.368 --> 33:01.675
My body is betraying me.

33:01.718 --> 33:04.025
♪ Tell me a story

33:04.069 --> 33:06.027
♪ Truth and the lying

33:06.071 --> 33:08.290
Death is just another door

33:08.334 --> 33:10.423
and I'm gonna walk
through it

33:10.466 --> 33:11.728
the way I walk
through every door

33:11.772 --> 33:15.428
my whole life --

33:15.471 --> 33:16.995
with my head held high.

33:17.038 --> 33:19.475
Sawyer Fredericks:
♪ Another

33:19.519 --> 33:20.868
In control.

33:20.911 --> 33:25.481
♪ Darling,
you don't have to go ♪

33:25.525 --> 33:27.440
You'll get it one day.

33:27.483 --> 33:29.311
♪ We will

33:29.355 --> 33:31.444
♪ Oh, we will

33:31.487 --> 33:33.489
I get it now.

33:33.533 --> 33:35.578
♪ Step out of the light

33:35.622 --> 33:38.842
♪ And live like shadows

33:38.886 --> 33:42.020
♪ And where you go,
I'll follow ♪

33:42.063 --> 33:43.804
♪ And I won't

33:43.847 --> 33:48.026
Captain, this is Dr. Leighton.
He was Bridget's surgeon.

33:48.069 --> 33:49.723
-Hi.
-Hi.

33:49.766 --> 33:51.333
It was
a complicated surgery,

33:51.377 --> 33:53.727
but we were able
to repair the artery

33:53.770 --> 33:55.598
and save her arm.
-Thank you so much.

33:55.642 --> 33:57.339
She'll need to be with us
for a while,

33:57.383 --> 33:58.732
but she should be fine.

33:58.775 --> 34:01.039
Back to fighting fires
in no time.

34:01.082 --> 34:02.823
♪♪

34:02.866 --> 34:04.651
Never thought I'd say this,

34:04.694 --> 34:06.522
but maybe it's time
for her to stop.

34:06.566 --> 34:09.786
If you weren't my dad, I would
kick your ass for saying that.

34:09.830 --> 34:12.050
[ Chuckles ]

34:12.093 --> 34:13.877
Honey...

34:13.921 --> 34:15.749
Bridget...

34:15.792 --> 34:17.490
I believe in you.

34:17.533 --> 34:20.058
I know you can do
anything,

34:20.101 --> 34:23.061
but...

34:23.104 --> 34:25.846
I never should have dragged you
into the family business.

34:25.889 --> 34:29.937
You think you're gonna
stop me?

34:29.980 --> 34:33.506
I'm a Kozelek.

34:33.549 --> 34:34.681
It's in our blood.

34:34.724 --> 34:37.118
♪ ...that feeds your fire

34:37.162 --> 34:40.730
♪ And watch your flames
grow higher ♪

34:40.774 --> 34:42.515
-Ready for some visitors?
-Oh, oh, oh.

34:42.558 --> 34:45.735
Come on in, guys.

34:45.779 --> 34:47.781
♪ And we will

34:47.824 --> 34:49.913
Oh, God. Who let you guys in?

34:49.957 --> 34:51.480
[ Laughter ]

34:51.524 --> 34:53.134
♪ And live like shadows

34:53.178 --> 34:57.399
♪ And where you go,
I'll follow ♪

34:57.443 --> 35:01.142
♪ And I won't

35:01.186 --> 35:02.535
♪ Let this...

35:02.578 --> 35:04.580
What can I do for you,
Dr. Savetti?

35:04.624 --> 35:05.929
Are you gonna fire me?

35:05.973 --> 35:08.410
No.

35:08.454 --> 35:10.673
Is that it?

35:10.717 --> 35:13.415
It's not that I don't like
having Ariel around.

35:13.459 --> 35:15.025
She's actually pretty cool,
but --

35:15.069 --> 35:16.940
You're here to be
a doctor.

35:16.984 --> 35:20.770
♪ All that was lost

35:20.814 --> 35:23.904
But aren't we more
than that?

35:23.947 --> 35:25.949
If we're a family,

35:25.993 --> 35:29.997
and I like to think
that's what we are,

35:30.040 --> 35:33.000
shouldn't we be able
to ask more of each other?

35:33.043 --> 35:37.135
♪ I know it's hard

35:37.178 --> 35:40.877
I'm struggling.

35:40.921 --> 35:43.053
You can see it.

35:43.097 --> 35:45.969
♪ The life we could make

35:46.013 --> 35:48.537
I just need
a little bit more.

35:48.581 --> 35:51.975
♪ And we will

35:52.019 --> 35:55.153
♪ Oh, we will

35:55.196 --> 35:57.067
♪ Step out of the light

35:57.111 --> 35:59.809
♪ And live like shadows

35:59.853 --> 36:03.813
♪ And where you go,
I'll follow ♪

36:03.857 --> 36:06.990
♪ And I won't

36:07.034 --> 36:10.168
I have to find him.

36:10.211 --> 36:12.953
[ Faintly ] Hey. Good news.

36:12.996 --> 36:15.173
-We managed to save your leg.
-Caleb: Daddy!

36:15.216 --> 36:16.783
Terrence: Caleb!

36:16.826 --> 36:19.481
I don't feel anything.

36:19.525 --> 36:22.180
-That's the morphine.
-No, it's not.

36:22.223 --> 36:23.659
Please, he's still out there.

36:23.703 --> 36:25.487
-Dad!
-You have to find him!

36:25.531 --> 36:28.229
Caleb: Where are you?!
Dad!

36:28.273 --> 36:29.665
♪♪

36:29.709 --> 36:32.668
Caleb!

36:32.712 --> 36:34.104
Daddy!

36:34.148 --> 36:36.498
He must be so scared!

36:36.542 --> 36:38.500
I can't leave Caleb!

36:38.544 --> 36:41.111
-I need help!
-Daddy.

36:41.155 --> 36:43.113
Caleb: Is my daddy here?

36:43.157 --> 36:45.551
♪ We will

36:45.594 --> 36:47.248
Caleb:
Where's my daddy?

36:47.292 --> 36:49.859
♪ Oh, we will

36:49.903 --> 36:52.035
♪ Step out of the light

36:52.079 --> 36:55.082
♪ And live like shadows

36:55.125 --> 36:56.997
-[ Sobbing ]
-Daddy!

36:57.040 --> 36:59.129
Oh! [ Sobbing ]

36:59.173 --> 37:01.784
There's a little
smoke inhalation,
but he's gonna be fine.

37:01.828 --> 37:04.091
♪ Be no trouble

37:04.134 --> 37:06.267
[ Sobbing ]

37:06.311 --> 37:07.660
I love you, Daddy.

37:07.703 --> 37:09.705
[ Sobbing ]

37:09.749 --> 37:11.098
♪ Feeds your fire

37:11.141 --> 37:13.579
I love you, Caleb.

37:13.622 --> 37:16.973
♪ Flames grow higher
and I won't ♪Thank you.

37:17.017 --> 37:22.065
♪ No, I won't

37:22.109 --> 37:24.024
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-I need a drink.

37:24.067 --> 37:26.244
First round's on me.

37:26.287 --> 37:28.681
I can't.

37:28.724 --> 37:30.291
Really? With the kind of
a day we just had?

37:30.335 --> 37:33.555
I told my aunt
I'd stop by.

37:33.599 --> 37:36.036
Guess I'm drinking
by myself.

37:36.079 --> 37:39.561
Go home, Ethan.

37:39.605 --> 37:40.823
Terrence would have never
been the same

37:40.867 --> 37:42.869
if he had lost his son.

37:42.912 --> 37:45.088
Cut your dad some slack.

37:45.132 --> 37:47.439
He's there now.

37:47.482 --> 37:49.615
He's trying.

37:49.658 --> 37:53.706
♪♪

37:53.749 --> 37:56.535
Are you serious?
They're gonna write us up?

37:56.578 --> 37:58.232
The judge is gonna hear
about what I did?

37:58.276 --> 38:00.626
Don't worry. I won't let it
jeopardize your adoption.

38:00.669 --> 38:04.238
How?Well...you'll have to stop
working here.

38:04.282 --> 38:06.327
-What? No.
-Ariel, it's one --

38:06.371 --> 38:08.503
No, I messed up today,
but I have to stay here.

38:08.547 --> 38:11.332
You do? Why?

38:11.376 --> 38:13.421
[ Sighs ]

38:13.465 --> 38:16.511
Because I want
to be a doctor.

38:16.555 --> 38:20.080
♪♪

38:20.123 --> 38:22.561
You never told me that
before.

38:22.604 --> 38:25.607
Because I never felt that
before.

38:25.651 --> 38:29.089
Well, okay, but, uh...

38:29.132 --> 38:31.221
[ Coughs ]

38:31.265 --> 38:32.745
Ariel, honey, are you okay?
What is it?

38:32.788 --> 38:35.095
[ Coughs ] I've been
having trouble breathing

38:35.138 --> 38:36.749
on and off for two days,

38:36.792 --> 38:39.099
and then fevers started today.
-Okay.

38:39.142 --> 38:41.667
I can hardly catch
my breath between breathing.

38:41.710 --> 38:43.277
Pneumonia.

38:43.321 --> 38:44.583
Beep! Wrong. Pertussis.

38:44.626 --> 38:45.758
Pertussis is a kind
of pneumonia.

38:45.801 --> 38:47.237
No, you're not specific.
I'm sorry.

38:47.281 --> 38:48.587
You didn't ask me
to be specific.

38:48.630 --> 38:51.285
Do you think the medical board
will care? No excuses.

38:51.329 --> 38:53.113
♪♪

38:53.156 --> 38:56.508
Hey. Wanna go to Hector's?
Two for one tacos.

38:56.551 --> 38:58.248
I don't know.
I work upstairs now.

38:58.292 --> 39:00.425
Hey, I was a jerk.

39:02.818 --> 39:06.387
Okay? An idiot. Imbecile.

39:06.431 --> 39:09.390
And, uh...

39:09.434 --> 39:11.479
I do wanna hear
how it went with, uh...

39:11.523 --> 39:13.394
you know who.

39:13.438 --> 39:15.701
Dr. Leighton, get in here.

39:15.744 --> 39:17.398
[ Whispers ]
Just not right now.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.487
Yeah. [ Clears throat ]

39:19.531 --> 39:21.794
Hey...be cool.

39:21.837 --> 39:23.622
[ Pats chest ]

39:23.665 --> 39:25.711
[ Sighs ]

39:30.193 --> 39:31.630
Don't say anything.
Just sit down.

39:37.723 --> 39:39.333
[ Pen clicks ]

39:43.555 --> 39:47.689
My daughter collapsed
during a field trip.

39:49.561 --> 39:52.215
They took her
to the hospital.

39:52.259 --> 39:55.305
She was alone,
begging me to come,

39:55.349 --> 39:58.526
but I couldn't leave
the hospital

39:58.570 --> 40:03.183
until another attending surgeon
could cover me.

40:03.226 --> 40:06.752
So in the meantime,
she called her mom.

40:06.795 --> 40:10.886
She hasn't seen
or talked to Felicia in years.

40:12.584 --> 40:16.196
I didn't even know Emily
had her number.

